  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A multicentre randomized controlled trial that will be conducted at Level 1 trauma centres
      across Canada. It will compare patients who receive open reduction, internal fixation for
      Sanders IV calcaneal fractures to patients who receive primary subtalar fusion for the same
      type of fracture. Patients will be followed up for a period of two years from the time of
      operation with evaluations being performed at 5 time points: 6 weeks, 3 months, 6 months, 12
      months, and 24 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
